I once heard a song called “ a serenade for a single mother” by Ziknei Tazfat about the pain in raising a small being against the gravity of this world without a man on your side. 

My mother used to laugh at me when I brought up complaints about her absence 

She used to smile in her freckled, warm way -turning soft all of a sudden with strange grace peaking from the creases of her tired face, and say to me: 

“You must have been raised by wolves.”

Beyond excited and honored to announce the release of my first film ARAVA (2023) World premiere at the festivals will be announced soon 🤍 working on this film was a process of years— stories from my adolescence in Jerusalem mixed with a writing collaboration with the amazing, talented @bzaharaa ✨starring Batel and my forever muse @swell_ariel.or ❤️ photo by the brilliant @thisismayan ❤️ graphic design by @stastuchinsky 
I want to thank everyone who believed in the project when I never even made a film before, to @keren.z.bergman Amir Nehoshet Schreiber, @michaeluchenik @benzeiger @avik_dogtooth @_bug2000_ and the amazing cast and crew. 
You are truly all amazing and this couldn’t have happened without y’all. Bless.* If I didn’t tag someone please tell me and I will 🙏🏼 full credits announced in next post 😘

Super excited to announce that my directorial debut ARAVA is world premiering at Palm Springs International Festival within the Official Selection category and is nominated for best international film award💗 the screening will be on June 22nd 🔜✨🫣 @psfilmfest 
Thank you to all the talented people who made this happen. I am full of gratitude and have no words 🥺💖

// Premiere // "Arava deals with the 'neighbourhood people' and at-risk youth, and generally highlights communities that make up under-represented textures of Israeli society."

@sarahmeital discusses making an inclusive, diverse, non-stereotypical portrayal of Israel with her powerful coming-of-age road trip movie 'Arava', which tests the bonds of female friendship, orthodoxy within the community and finding yourself on pilgrimage. We also had the chance to talk about her previous work as a casting director, the issues of contemporary Israeli cinema, and working closely with DOP @keren.z.bergman to inject a fascinating sense of subjectivity into the filmmaking. 

Watch the short and read the full interview over at DN - LINK IN BIO ⏯️

Beautiful news and congrats @wilsonfache on the nomination to the Albert Londres Prize. Had the pleasure to photograph this unique and profoundly genuine piece on the aging Tel Aviv’s bus terminal for @mouvement_magazine 🙏🏼 a year ago I lived a five minute walk from there and as I came back home to pack my apartment after my mothers passing, this article came my way giving me a chance to say goodbye. Thank you for this very meaningful project. Thank you @jeanrochh 🩵

Honored to be presenting Arava at @molodist_kiff in Kyiv, Ukraine, and grateful to attend in person in support of this brave nation that despite of Russia’s ongoing war and crimes against Ukrainian culture and nation, is continuing to celebrate and grow cultural life. Honored to be included in this incredible program with three nominations for awards including best film in competition, film in category and the audience award. Looking forward to seeing Ukraine for the first time- especially since my grandparents on my mothers side came from Dorhobytch. If anyone is in town and want to attend in late October, let me know 🙏🏼 dates announced soon🪬
